            <p class="highlight">Set in the village of Wencun, China, this calligraphy library and workshop bridges past and present through hybrid construction approach. The building is rooted in traditional brickwork techniques, but integrates contemporary technologies to enhance ventilation and lighting.</p>
            <p>Inspired by Professor Wang Shu's daily calligraphy practice, I generated hundreds of hand-drawn, imaginary characters, letting gesture and repetition guide form. These marks, though unreadable, became a generative language for the architecture itself to influence proportions, rhythms, and porosity.</p>
