      <div class="project-content">
        <div class="project-row">
          <div class="image-placeholder">syntax-axon-1.jpg</div>
          <div class="project-row-text">
            <p class="highlight">As part of my work with Low Design Office, I developed a tailored drawing syntax for LowDO, focused on efficiency and cohesion across the firm's diverse outputs.</p>
            <p>The system was developed using only Rhino3D and a single Photoshop filter for color adjustments, prioritizing a streamlined digital workflow that minimizes complexity while maintaining clarity and precision in representational drawings.</p>
            <p>By establishing a unified set of graphic conventions, including standardized line weights, annotation styles, and consistent color palettes, the syntax enables rapid production and easy updates across all drawing types.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>Designed to be highly adaptable, this syntax extends beyond architectural drawings to construction schedule spreadsheets and the firm's future website, ensuring a consistent visual language throughout all LowDO materials. The straightforward digital process supports quick iteration, allowing legacy projects to be efficiently revamped and integrated with new work. Over a period of just a few days, this protocol was used to reformat and visually unify a complete slate of previous LowDO projects, resulting in a seamless portfolio that conveys design intent with a cohesive brand identity.</p>

